# Permutations MCP — Project Rules for AI Agents

These rules govern how AI coding agents (Cursor, Windsurf, Claude Desktop) must interact with this codebase. The Permutations MCP server is the single source of truth for all design decisions. **No aesthetic values may be invented manually.**

---

## Rule 1 — Always Call The Engine First

Before creating any new UI component, page, section or design token, you MUST call the `generate_design_genome` MCP tool.

```
{
  "tool": "generate_design_genome",
  "arguments": {
    "intent": "<describe the component or page in plain language>",
    "seed": "<project-name>-<component-name>-<timestamp>",
    "project_context": "<overarching brand or product narrative>",
    "brand_asset_paths": ["</absolute/path/to/logo.png>", "</absolute/path/to/brand-guidelines.pdf>"]
  }
}
```

`project_context` and `brand_asset_paths` are optional but STRONGLY recommended for contextual accuracy.

---

## Rule 2 — Apply The Generated Config

After calling the tool, you will receive a JSON response with multiple output fields. Apply each one:

### `tailwindConfig`
Copy this into `tailwind.config.js`. Do not merge manually — replace the `theme.extend` section entirely.

### `cssVariableBlock` (from the `css` format output)
Inject these CSS custom properties into `index.css` under `:root`. These are the live design tokens.

### `webglComponents`
If `ch18_rendering.primary` is `webgl`, paste the generated JSX into a `Procedural3D.tsx` file.

### `fxAtmosphere`
Paste the generated `.fx-atmosphere` CSS class into `index.css`. Apply the class to your hero/section containers.

### `svgBiomarker`
Use the generated SVG as the brand mark in your navbar/header. Do not substitute a generic icon.

---

## Rule 3 — Respect Forbidden Patterns

The `genome.constraints.forbiddenPatterns` array contains patterns you are **strictly prohibited from using**.

Common examples and what they mean:
| Pattern | What to avoid |
|---|---|
| `large_hero_images` | No full-bleed background images in hero sections |
| `scroll_animations` | No scroll-triggered fade/parallax effects |
| `bounce_animations` | No spring-easing on bouncy elements |
| `rounded_cards` | No heavily rounded cards (border-radius must be 0 or genome-defined) |
| `heavy_blur_effects` | No backdrop-filter or gaussian blur greater than genome intensity |
| `generous_whitespace` | No padding > genome-unit * 2 between sections |

---

## Rule 4 — Respect Required Patterns

The `genome.constraints.requiredPatterns` array contains patterns you **must implement**.

Common examples:
| Pattern | What to implement |
|---|---|
| `high_contrast_text` | All body text must meet the `minContrastRatio` from ch17_accessibility |
| `tabular_numerals` | All numbers must use `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums` |
| `compact_base_spacing` | Use `genome-unit` (from ch2) as the base spacing unit everywhere |

---

## Rule 5 — Typography Must Use Genome Values

Do not invent font sizes. Use the `fontSize.*` values from the generated Tailwind config:
- `text-display` for hero headings
- `text-h1`, `text-h2`, `text-h3` for hierarchy
- `text-body` for paragraphs
- `text-small` for captions and metadata

Font families are defined by `ch3_type_display.family` (headings) and `ch4_type_body.family` (body text). Do not use fonts not in these families.

---

## Rule 6 — Color Is Derived From The Genome

The primary color is defined by `ch5_color_primary`. Never use hex/RGB colors that are not derived from this chromosome. Use `var(--primary-hue)`, `var(--primary-sat)`, `var(--primary-light)` in CSS, or the `primary` Tailwind token.

Background colors are defined by `ch6_color_temp.backgroundTemp`:
- `cool` → dark backgrounds (`#0a0a0a`, `#141414`)
- `warm` → light backgrounds (`#fafaf9`, `#ffffff`)
- `neutral` → medium tone

---

## Rule 7 — Motion Must Respect The Genome

Use `transition-timing-function: var(--genome-easing)` and `transition-duration: var(--genome-duration)` for all animations.
If `ch17_accessibility.respectMotionPreference` is `true`, wrap all animations with `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference)`.

---

## When To Re-Run The Engine

- When starting a new feature area (e.g. switching from landing page to dashboard)
- When the user provides brand assets (logos, style guides)
- Never re-run with the same seed for the same component unless you want deterministic regeneration
